The paper discusses recent advances in deep reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The experiments are conducted on Atari games, which involve computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The paper also proposes an optimization strategy, which involves neural networks (cs.NE) and deep learning (cs.DL) techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, and cs.DL.
